{#
  hx-tooltip — Drupal Twig Template
  ===================================

  Server-renders the hx-tooltip custom element with correct attributes.
  Show/hide behavior (hover, focus, keyboard) is handled automatically
  by the component — no Drupal behavior is required for standard usage.

  Note on htmx: If your project uses htmx, be aware that `hx-*` attribute names are
  reserved by htmx. The `hx-tooltip` tag and `placement`, `show-delay`, and `hide-delay`
  attributes do not conflict with htmx directives, but avoid adding other `hx-*`
  attributes that htmx may interpret as directives.

  Parameters:
    trigger_label  (string)  Required. Visible label for the trigger element.
    content        (string)  Required. Tooltip text content.
    placement      (string)  Optional. Preferred tooltip placement relative to the trigger.
                             Supports all Floating UI placement values:
                             top | top-start | top-end | bottom | bottom-start | bottom-end
                             left | left-start | left-end | right | right-start | right-end
                             Defaults to 'top'.
    show_delay     (int)     Optional. Milliseconds before the tooltip appears. Defaults to 300.
    hide_delay     (int)     Optional. Milliseconds before the tooltip disappears. Defaults to 100.
    trigger_type   (string)  Optional. Button type attribute: button | submit | reset.
                             Defaults to 'button'.
    aria_label     (string)  Optional. Accessible name for icon-only triggers where
                             trigger_label is not visible (e.g. icon buttons).
    attributes     (object)  Optional. Additional HTML attributes to spread onto the element.

  Slots (Twig blocks):
    trigger — The trigger element rendered in the default slot.
    content — The tooltip text rendered in the content slot.

  Usage examples:

    Basic tooltip on a button:
      {% include 'hx-tooltip.twig' with {
        trigger_label: 'View Details',
        content: 'Opens the patient record in a new panel.',
      } %}

    Custom placement:
      {% include 'hx-tooltip.twig' with {
        trigger_label: 'Lab Results',
        content: 'Most recent CBC panel from 2026-03-10.',
        placement: 'bottom-start',
      } %}

    Instant show (no delay):
      {% include 'hx-tooltip.twig' with {
        trigger_label: 'Help',
        content: 'Contact your administrator for access.',
        show_delay: 0,
        hide_delay: 0,
      } %}

    Icon-only trigger (accessible name required):
      {% include 'hx-tooltip.twig' with {
        trigger_label: '',
        aria_label: 'More information',
        content: 'Blood pressure measured in the left arm.',
      } %}

  No Drupal behavior required:
    The component manages tooltip visibility entirely via its shadow DOM event handlers.
    Standard usage requires no Drupal.behaviors attachment. For custom interactions
    (e.g. programmatic show/hide from a Drupal behavior), access the element directly:

      (function (Drupal, once) {
        Drupal.behaviors.helixTooltip = {
          attach: function (context) {
            once('hx-tooltip-custom', 'hx-tooltip[data-custom]', context).forEach((el) => {
              // Components expose no public show/hide methods — control via focus/hover
              // events on the slotted trigger element if programmatic control is needed.
            });
          },
        };
      })(Drupal, once);
#}

<hx-tooltip
  {% if placement is defined and placement %}placement="{{ placement }}"{% endif %}
  {% if show_delay is defined %}show-delay="{{ show_delay }}"{% endif %}
  {% if hide_delay is defined %}hide-delay="{{ hide_delay }}"{% endif %}
  {% for key, val in attributes|default({}) %}{{ key }}="{{ val }}" {% endfor %}
>
  {%- block trigger -%}
    <button
      type="{{ trigger_type|default('button') }}"
      {% if aria_label %}aria-label="{{ aria_label }}"{% endif %}
    >{{ trigger_label }}</button>
  {%- endblock -%}
  {%- block content -%}
    <span slot="content">{{ content }}</span>
  {%- endblock -%}
</hx-tooltip>
